{"name": "Smith Zoom Junior Snow Helmet - Children to Youths", "categories": ["Home", "All", "Ski and snowboard gear", "Ski and snowboard helmets", "Zoom Junior Snow Helmet"], "description": "The soft, furry lining is pure fun. The lightweight shell offers solid secure protection.Lightweight in-mold construction with a polycarbonate shell and an EPS inner.AirEvac2 system drives warm air away from goggles and adjusts by folding or unfolding liner flaps.Fit system adjusts with the twist of dial.Softy, furry tricot lining is removable and machine washable.Helmet and removable goggle clip are contoured to match the curve of Smith goggles for gap-free coverage.", "product_code": "5043-656", "tech_specs": {"Weight": ["350g (Youth Medium)"], "Ideal for": ["Downhill skiing", "Snowboarding"], "Construction\n\nMicroshell helmets are made of a thin polymer sheet over a foam liner; Hardshell helmets have a hard polymer outer shell and a foam liner; when the liner is being bonded to the outer shell during the manufacturing process, it is Molded in the shell.": ["Molded in the shell"], "Shell material": ["Polycarbonate"], "Fit system": ["Adjustable dial"], "Inner material": ["EPS (expanded polystyrene)"], "Vents": ["Yes"], "Goggle clip": ["Yes"], "Removable ear liners": ["Yes"], "Approved for\n\nMost helmets are tested and certified for a specific sport. Some helmets are approved for multi-sports, but only after passing the safety tests for both sports (i.e., snowsports and cycling).": ["Snowsports"], "Safety rating\n\nCetification is established by a variety of governing bodies who set impact standards. Most helmets are certified or approved for a specific sport, except in the case of multi-sport helmets (i.e., a snowsports helmet might also be approved for cycling if it meets the cycling safety standards).": ["ASTM F2040", "EN 1077: 2007"], "Made in": ["China"]}, "img_urls": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9131591237662/5043656-THS00.jpg"]}